org.ipdr.collector.configuration
Class CollectorConfigXml

java.lang.Object
  org.ipdr.api.configuration.CollectorConfigBase
      org.ipdr.collector.configuration.CollectorConfigXml
All Implemented Interfaces:
CollectorConfigI
public class CollectorConfigXml
extends CollectorConfigBase

The class contains an implementation of CollectorConfigI, which reads the configuration from an XML file. The xml file has the following structure:

<IPDRcollectorConfiguration xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"> <Collector IP="10.1.100.81" templateNegotiation="true" supportDiscovery="false" port="4737" startInterval="30" protocolVersion="2" vendor="IPDR" acceptTimeout="30" strictTemplates="false" udpDiscoveryTimeout="3" udpDiscoveryPort="4737"/> <Exporters> <Exporter IP="10.1.100.14"> <Connection type="passive" count="1" connectTimeOut="100" keepAlive="20" port="15200" retryCount="1" retryInterval="1"> <Description>Connection's description </Description> <Sessions> <Session id="1" name="mySession1"> <Description>Session's description1 </Description> <TemplateRefs> <TemplateRef ref="1"> <TemplateConfig> <FieldConfig keyId="101" fieldUsed="false"/> <FieldConfig keyId="102" fieldUsed="true"/> <FieldConfig keyId="103" fieldUsed="true"/> </TemplateConfig> </TemplateRef> </TemplateRefs> </Session> </Sessions> </Connection> </Exporter> </Exporters> <Templates> <Template globalRef="111" id="1"> <Description>Template's description 1 </Description> <Fields> <Field keyId="101" fieldUsed="true" keyName="myKey1" keyTypeId="33"></Field> <Field keyId="102" fieldUsed="true" keyName="myKey2" keyTypeId="33"></Field> <Field keyId="103" fieldUsed="true" keyName="myKey3" keyTypeId="40"></Field> </Fields> </Template> </Templates> </IPDRcollectorConfiguration> The configuration file has three top-level tags: <Collector> for collector configuration, <Exporters> for exporter configuration, <Templates> for templates configuration. The collector configuration is in the attributes of <Collector> element:
IP
Collector IP address
port
Collector listening TCP port
templateNegotiation
Template negotiation capability
supportDiscovery
UDP discovery support
startInterval
Start interval for connection spawning
protocolVersion
Collector default protocol version
vendor
Vendor string
acceptTimeout
Accept timeout
strictTemplates
Strict templates flag
udpDiscoveryTimeout
Timeout for UDP discovery
udpDiscoveryPort
UDP port for incoming discovery requests
Each exporter is represented as a <Exporter> element. It has a single attribute, IP, which contains its IP address. Specific connections of an exporter are configured in child <Connection> elements. Each <Connection> element has the following attributes:
type
"active" or "passive", according to the connection type
count
Maximum count for the connection. Only meaningful for passive connections.
connectTimeOut
Connect timeout
retryCount
Number of connection attempt retries. Defaults to infinite
retryInterval
Interval between connection retries
keepAlive
Expected keepalive timeout
port
TCP port to connect to. Only meaningful for active connections.
Under each <Connection> element, there is a <Description> child element which contains verbal description of the connection. There is also a <Sessions> tag, which contains a list of sessions on this connection. Each such session is represented as <Session> element. The <Session> element has the following attributes:
id
Numeric id of the session
name
Name of the session
Each <Session> has a child <Description> element with verbal description of the session. It also has a child <TemplateRefs> element, which contains template references for negotiation purposes. Each template reference is represented by a <TemplateRef> element, which has the only attribute ref. The attribute holds an id of the template. Each <TemplateRef> has a child <TemplateConfig> element so that for Each field that is referenced the <TemplateConfig> contains a child <FiledConfig> element with the following attributes:
keyId
Numeric id of the field
fieldUsed
When negotiated, the collectors decision whether to enabled the field for output
The <Templates> top-level element holds description of known templates. Each template is represented by a <Template> element. The tag must have an id attribute, which should hold a numeric value of the template id. Under the <Template>, tags <Description> and <Fields> are expected to be found. The <Description> holds the verbal description of the template. The <Fields> tag holds enumeration of template fields. Each field is represented by a <Field> tag. Each such tag must have the following attributes:
keyId
Numeric id of the field
fieldUsed
Is the field enabled for output by default
keyName
Name of the field
keyTypeId
Type id of the field
